    <h2> Article 2: ‘Infuriated’ Trump Considers New Unilateral Steps To Boost Economy, Pushing Back Tax Deadline Even Further, May 8th 2020, the Daily Wire </h2>
    <p1>Summary: This article written by James Barrett is  about President Trump pushing back tax deadlines to help Americans during the Pandemic. The article begins with him explaining Amid the ongoing economic devastation of widespread shutdowns in response to the COVID-19 pandemic, the White House is considering taking unilateral steps to try to shore up the crippled economy, including extending the federal tax filing deadline even further — to as late as Dec. 15. He talks about how the deadline depends on how and when businesses open back up. He talks about how Trump is getting infuriated with the amount the unemployment rate is rising as before the pandemic Trump had gotten the unemployment rate to one of the lowest its ever been, for all races and both genders.</p1>
    <p2>Course Content: This article can be related to the COVID-19 case study we wrote an essay on. Many businesses are having to shut down or lay off employees which is causing millions to go unemployed and is crippling America. But for someone like President Trump, America is like his business and he's trying to keep people employees. But he’s got one huge problem on his shoulders and that the democrats. The democrats keep blocking Trump from funding small businesses and getting money to the people and the democrats are using the covid funding to fund their own parties' ideas. It’s absolutely pathetic. I understand how Trump is infuriated, while hes working non-stop to get these Americans help, the democrats are spending time and money to make lies about him and to fund their ideas such as the green new deal. Big companies as well as small companies are shutting down forcing people to go broke. Like business owners are doing things for covid-19, Trump has put travel bans into place, sent money to bail out small businesses.</p2>
    
